Method Detail

getViewExternal

public static void getViewExternal(javax.media.j3d.View view,
                                   javax.vecmath.Point3d pos,
                                   javax.media.j3d.Transform3D xform)
Extracts and returns the external geometry in world space of the specified view. The view position is at the center eye in the display canvas and its orientation is that of the view platform.

Parameters:
view - The target view. Never null.
pos - Return view position. Null if none.
xform - Return view external transform. Null if none.

getNodeExternal

public static void getNodeExternal(javax.media.j3d.Node node,
                                   javax.vecmath.Point3d pos,
                                   javax.media.j3d.Transform3D xform)
Extracts and returns the external geometry in world space of the specified node. The node position is at its origin. The node must be set with ALLOW_LOCAL_TO_VWORLD_READ.

Parameters:
node - The target node. Never null.
pos - Return node position. Null if none.
xform - Return node external transform. Null if none.

getOrientation

public static void getOrientation(javax.media.j3d.Transform3D xform,
                                  javax.vecmath.AxisAngle4d rot,
                                  javax.vecmath.Vector3d dir,
                                  javax.vecmath.Vector3d up)
Gets the orientation of an object from its external geometric transform.

Parameters:
xform - The external transform. Never null.
rot - Copy of the output rotation. Null if none.
dir - Copy of the output forward direction (along local space -Z axis). Null if none.
up - Copy of the output up direction (along local space Y axis). Null if none.
